    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<h2>Mistress Aldea Veren — Trina's Old Correspondent in the Wood</h2>\n<p><em>Half-elven retired scholar of pre-Aerdy paleography and sealing materials. Lives alone in a small stone cottage in a wooded valley a day's careful ride west of Loftwick. Will not travel. Reads what is in front of her; will not invent what is not.</em></p>\n<h3>Combat behavior</h3>\n<p><strong>Avoids.</strong> If her cottage is attacked she withdraws into the workshop, bars the door, and uses a small bell-rope (which summons her brindle dog, the great horned owl, and three guardian creatures the party should not fight unless prepared for a hard tier-2 encounter; treat as Awakened Treant CR 2 reskinned as a thicket-spirit, plus two Dire Wolves loyal to the valley). She will not initiate.</p>\n<h3>Statblock summary (CR 1/4, PB +2)</h3>\n<p>AC 12 · HP 22 (5d8) · Speed 30 ft. · Init +1 · Passive Perception 14</p>\n<p>STR 10 · DEX 12 · CON 11 · INT 18 · WIS 16 · CHA 14. Saves: INT +6, WIS +5. Skills: Arcana +6, History +6, Insight +5, Investigation +6, Nature +5, Perception +5.</p>\n<p>Senses: Darkvision 60 ft. (half-elf), Passive Perception 14. Languages: Common, Elvish, Old Aerdi, Suloise, Yeomanry diplomatic + southern Suel trade ciphers, three additional ancient scripts.</p>\n<h3>Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fey Ancestry.</strong> Advantage on saves vs. being charmed; magic cannot put her to sleep.</li>\n<li><strong>Reader of Hands.</strong> Identifies era, region, and likely paleographic school of any document she has time to study (one hour minimum); identifies the recipe-family of any sealing wax she can examine in person.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p><em>Blooming Rot, Part 2 — Phase 5.</em> See <em>Phase 5 — Loftwick NPCs → Mistress Aldea Veren</em> for full profile and the right question.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
